        <h2>About Me</h2>
        <p>I am a Southern Miss graduate who lettered 4 years. I have a clothing brand that I design for and plan events. I have organized 10+ events in New Orleans and created products for musical artists, painters, and business owners. One of my larger projects was helping FLVR (a PepsiCo brand) with its inaugural merch drop. I also designed a mock t-shirt for Trinidad James' inaugural drop of Hommewrk, which gave me the opportunity to attend ComplexCon as a special guest.</p>
        <p>I have received orders from 30+ countries around the world, worked with Sneaker Politics, and been a one-time vendor at this premier sneaker boutique in the South. I have also collaborated with Grammy-nominated artist Pell, renowned artists Jay McKay and Cubsthepoet, and Tyrell Shaw, all located in New Orleans. These relationships were cultivated genuinely through a friend at Wayne Clark, the owner of Mr. Wolf Espresso.</p>
